  "text": "For the 14 potential BPA replacement compounds that were predicted to be ER binders, their binding affinities were further estimated using the quantitative prediction model developed in our previous study [CITATION_1] . The quantitative predictions are given in the last column of Table 1 . Most of these 14 compounds were predicted as weak ER binders with estimated binding affinities similar to the experimentally determined binding affinity for the reference compound, BPA. Only compound 8 showed more than 100 fold higher ER binding affinity than BPA; but the consensus qualitative DF model had a low prediction confidence level. Compound 16 has a relatively large size and its molecular shape could not fit into the ER ligand binding pocket that was adopted from an ER complex bound with an ER agonist in the protein data bank. It failed in the docking and, thus, its ER binding affinity could not be estimated using this quantitative prediction model. Therefore, compound 16 is likely a non-binder based on the docking model though it was predicted to an ER binder at low confidence 0.584.",
